post_text: Hello everyone on LinkedIn! Today I'd like to share my experience with a project I've been working on as a Junior+ Python web developer.The project is a web application that helps people manage their expenses. It allows users to add their income, expenses, and view statistics on their spending. It was developed using the Flask framework and PostgreSQL for the database.One of the challenges I faced during this project was designing the database schema. I had to ensure that the tables and relationships between them were set up in a way that would allow for efficient querying and easy maintenance. Additionally, I had to implement authentication and authorization to ensure that users could only access their own data.Another challenge was developing the user interface. I wanted to make it as user-friendly as possible, while also ensuring that it looked clean and professional. I used HTML, CSS, and Bootstrap for the front-end development, and JavaScript for some additional functionality.Despite the challenges, I am proud of what I was able to accomplish. It was rewarding to see the project come together and be used by real people. I also learned a lot about project management and working with a team, as I collaborated with other developers and a project manager to complete the project.Overall, this project was a great experience and it reinforced my passion for Python and web development. I'm excited to continue working on projects like this and to learn more along the way.Thanks for reading and I'd love to hear about your experiences with web development or any interesting projects you're working on. Let's connect and grow together! #team #webdevelopment #python #development #webdeveloper #project #opentowork #hunting #work #share #like #linkedin #projectmanagement #people #projects #maintenance #database #experience #statistics #html #css #javascript #data #love # # # #

My name is Hakob and I am excited to introduce myself as a Junior+ Python web developer.I'm sure you're already aware of how popular Python is in the programming world.
